public class Triple<A,B,C> extends Object implements Tuple3<A,B,C>
The tuple with only three elements. The Triple class implements Tuple3 and provides all his behaviour.

    • equals

      public boolean equals(Object obj)
      Indicates whether some other Object is "equal to" this one.
      Overrides:
      equals in class Object
      ImplSpec:
      This implementation will return true, if one of the following conditions is true:
      1. This tuple and obj argument refer to the same Object object
      2. This tuple and obj argument has the same type, i.e. booth are the realisation of the Tuple3 tuple with size = 3. And all values of this tuple has the same order and equals to values of the obj argument (T = B if (t0, t1, t2) = (b0, b1, b2) and |T| = |B| = 3)
      Parameters:
      obj - the reference object with which to compare.
      Returns:
      true if this tuple is the same as the obj argument; false otherwise.
